1) "My hobbies". Vocabulary: fields of sport, music and other hobbies. Grammar: -ma and -da- infinitive, sufix mine, verb "tegelema", mas-, mast-forms and their usage;
2) "Dream job". Vobabulary: occupations, places of employment, activities. Grammar: translative and essive cases, noun cases: terminative, essive, abessive, comitative, cases in plural; 
3) "This is a great trip". Vocabulary: sightseeing in Estonia and abroad, organizing a trip, buying tickets, finding accommodation. Grammar: locative cases, comparative and superlative, ordinals and cardinals.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This is a short course that continues to develop the students'  basic knowledge of grammatical structures and spoken language. The aim of the course is to practice the basics of  Estonian grammar and  vocabulary. The intended outcome of the course is  level A.2.1 ( pre-intermediate)  in all the language skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the students will be able  * to understand and use Estonian cases,  conjugate Estonian verbs in the present and past tenses, compare adjectives and use cardinal and ordinal numbers, * to communicate in everyday situations in the street, in a shop, at a restaurant and  socialize in a group,  talk and write about her/himself, her/his job, hobbies, important days in her/ his life,  express (dis)approval. * to understand and  create  elementary-level oral and written texts.
